    "text": "Yes, it helped — that 8.5 hours did real work, comfortably above your 7-day average of 6.8 hours — but one long night doesn't clear the ledger: you're still carrying about 130 minutes of sleep debt. The catch-up itself was the right move; the mistake would be treating it as the fix. This week, repetition pays the rest down: keep your wake time fixed even on days you get to bed late, and if you nap, cap it around 30 minutes and keep it before mid-afternoon so it doesn't push bedtime back. Chip the remaining debt in modest nightly slices rather than banking on another big weekend night.",
